efonica SpA says that negotiations are near completionwith Cuba on an agreement to manage the country's international phonenetwork: it also claims that it will probably receive contracts fromVenezuela when that country completes the privatisation of its telecommssector.andM;- o -andM;Advanced RISC Machines Ltd has turned to European Silicon Structures Ltd,ES2, as an alternate source to VLSI Technology Inc: it says that ES2 hasdelivered prototypes of the forthcoming ARM3 RISC CPU.andM;- o -andM;Matsushita Electric Works Ltd has set up a research centre in San Jose,California costing, $600,000, to study both semiconductor and computersoftware technologies.andM;- o -andM;Telefon AB LM Ericsson is laying off 100 employees at its Kristianstad plantin Sweden which makes parts for the public telecommunications businesssector: meanwhile Ericsson says it has won contracts with a combined value of$78m to expand the mobile networks in Singapore, Indonesia and Malaysia.andM;- o -andM;Matsushita subsidiary Kyushu Matsushita Electric Co is setting up a researchand development centre for satellite communications and computer software inResearch Triangle, North Carolina: the Kyushu Matsushita Electric ResearchLab will be set up in December at an initial start-up cost of $742,000.andM;- o -andM;Hewlett-Packard Co is planning to unveil a new generation of microcomputerson Thursday: chairman John Young told a Paris news conference that the newmachines will be built in Grenoble, France, which is also headquarters forthe company's microcomputer business; he declined to give out any furtherdetails.andM;- o -andM;Recession - what recession? Advanced Micro Devices has distributed more than$2.9m to domestic employees in the company's profit sharing payout for thefirst half of 1991: the distribution, approximately half in cash and half indeferred compensation, was based on AMD's performance through June 30, 1991,when the company reported net income of $21.5m on $571m in sales.andM;- o -andM;GRiD Systems Corp of Fremont, California has expanded its internationaldistribution operations into the Pacific Rim by signing agreements with TCGof Sydney, Australia, Melbourne-based Vicom and Southmark of Auckland, NewZealand.andM;- o -andM;In the UK, Informix Software Ltd has won a #240,000 order from the Departmentof Social Security to supply its database technology on one component of theDepartment's Single Terminal Access Project, known as STAP: the Informixdatabase will be used on the national personnel system at 159 benefit officesaround the country running on Siemens-Nixdorf Informationssysteme AG WX200Santa Crux Unix boxes and ICL Plc's DRS 6000s.andM;- o -andM;One of the wilder pieces of gossip doing the rounds that showed up in PCMagazine has IBM Corp getting into a huddle with Lotus Development Corp atwhich Lotus talks of developing a low-end operating system to replace MS-DOSfor IBM.andM;- o -andM;ICL Plc says that an order from Northern Telecom Ltd for Unix officeautomation software for 3,000 users at 10 locations is its biggest yet forOfficePower 6.50 - but no value was given for the order, which includes 32 ofICL's DRS 6000 Sparc-based business machines.andM;- o -andM;Apple Computer Inc has bought distribution rights from Connectix Corp for itsMode32 utility, which will be offered free to users of the Macintosh II, IIx,IIcx, and SE/30 so that they can access the virtual memory addressingfeatures of System 7.0: according to Microbytes, the utility is necessarybecause the ROMs in these models are not able to execute 32-bit addressing,and enables users of 32-bit-unclean Macs access up to 128Mb of physical RAMusing System 7 and Mac II users up to 72Mb, which was not possible previouslyon these four systems; it is not needed for the Mac LC, IIci, IIsi, IIfx; itis not useful for non-virtual 68000 systems.andM;- o -andM;Swedish communications giant L M Ericsson Telefon AB has adopted acompany-wide information technology policy that requires all of itssubsidiaries and operating companies to adopt systems that conform to X/OpenCo Ltd's Portability Guide 3 specifications in future.andM;- o -andM;The University of Western Australia, Nedlands, and the MassachusettsInstitute of Technology's Lincoln Laboratory, Lexington, Massachusetts, haveinstalled Star 910/VP high-end Sparc-based servers from Star TechnologiesInc, which has its base in Sterling, Virginia.andM;- o -andM;Munich-based Bayerische Motoren Werke AG, known on the road as BMW, hasrecently installed a supercomputer in the BMW research and development centrein Munich courtesy of Cray Research Inc: the eight processor Cray Y-MPsystem, with a 64M-word memory, replaces a Cray X-MP system and was installedin April; it will be used in the search for more fuel efficient products andbreakthroughs in the area of structural and fluid dynamics.andM;- o -andM;For Sale: two-ton racing yacht, Bruce Farr designed, custom built by GreenMarine, Lymington, one careful owner, only 8 months old, full Admirals Cupbodykit - international commitments and financial constraints force quicksale: serious offers only around $600,000 -#350,000 - for Wings of Oracle.andO;</TEXT></DOC>